import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Price')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat prices over the years?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'], label='Wheat Prices')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wages'], label='Wages')
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.title('How do wages compare to wheat prices over the years?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
